nihstro
------------------------------------------
nihstro is a collection of tools for 3DS shaders targeted at homebrew
development and/or reverse engineering. Currently, it supports assembling 3DS
shader binaries from assembly source code and disassembling shaders from shbin
files. It also provides C++ interfaces for analyzing and runtime-compiling
shaders.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libboost_program_options1.66-1.66.0-1
  libgcc1-7.3.0-2
  libstdc++6-7.3.0-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-7.3.0-2
  make-4.2.1-2
  ninja-1.8.2-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/neobrain/nihstro

Canonical download:
  git://github.com/neobrain/nihstro.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack nihstro-0.1+git20180114-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./nihstro-0.1+git20180114-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/nihstro-0.1+git20180114-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/nihstro-0.1+git20180114-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(nihstro)
  /usr/bin/nihstro-assemble.exe
  /usr/bin/nihstro-disassemble.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/nihstro.README
  /usr/share/doc/nihstro/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/nihstro/README.md

